description: For sale: $209,000. A Woodland Hilltop Traditional!  This timeless home is situated on a quiet tree-lined street on a larger city lot right in the heart of Woodland. The separate dining room has a beautiful buffet, new lighting and a sliding glass door that leads out to the brick patio and huge fenced in yard. A cheery county kitchen with newer appliances, butcher block countertop, contemporary shelves and ample space for the gourmet chef.  The back entrance is spacious with plenty of room and extra space for pantry overflow. Upstairs are the three bedrooms, nice sized and great closet space. The full bath is sizable and has a lovely claw foot tub!  Newer windows throughout the home. The newer two-car detached garage offers storage for cars, toys and lawn equipment. Imagine your housewarming party on the patio under the huge maple trees.  Living in Woodland you have easy access to  Hartely Field, Woodland Market Place, schools, biking, hiking, and skiing trails, fishing at the pond and just minutes from U of M and downtown.

description: For sale: $569,000. 3% commission to buyer's realtor.

description: For sale: $674,900. Your own Private Retreat!  This home REALLY does have it all....3 of the 6 bedrooms have their own private baths attached (your choice of 3 master bedrooms), the lower level has its own entrance (off garage) & a full kitchen such that it could be rented out or used as an in law apt. The workmanship & thoughtful layout of the house is second to none.  You can enjoy all the seasons in this luxury home: ski out your back door onto your own ski trails. Then enjoy a sauna or sit by the fire. You may even see the northern lights from the front yard & there are great sunset views from the front patio. Invite your friends over to catch the game & share a meal in the fully equipped sports bar in the lower level with a stove, oven, dishwasher & full size Viking refrigerator. The unique bar is made of reclaimed industrial lumber from Canada. After the game, head into the Theatre room for a feature film! Create gourmet delicacies in the expansive kitchen with its large sunny pantry. Amenities include: Sub Zero refrigerators, Sub Zero wine storage refrigerator with dual zones, gas stove top, pasta faucet over stove, double ovens, two sink stations, two Fisher-Paykel dishwashers. Plenty of room for large parties & festive gatherings - from wine tasting to Christmas feasts. Other features include: two 104 gallon high efficiency water heaters so everyone can have hot showers, three HVAC systems (Radiant Heat on each level, mini split heat/AC on each floor, Propane stove in Lower level), laundry rooms on main level as well as upper level for convenience, heated attached garage plus a heated detached garage (30x40), circular driveway, chicken coop with run, 5 year old apple orchard & a vegetable garden with gardening shed. description: Recently sold: $335,000. A roomy ranch on 11+ tranquil acres! Welcome to 7602 Pequaywan Lake Road, stepping into the oversized foyer where you are greeted by the warmth of the free-standing Franklin wood-burning stove and the ideal spot to remove boots and coats. The master suite has a 1/2 bath and ample sleeping and closets. The second of the four bedrooms are on this side (original) of the home. Enter into the family room very bright and sunny, a newly remodeled 3/4 bath, and two of the bedrooms all added to the home in 2014. Brand new flooring, newer lighting, and contemporary wall color make this home turn-key. The outdoor living space offers the deck for grilling and soaking up some sun, trails for hiking, biking, snowmobiling, skiing, and running. Just minutes away is Briars Lake, where you can fish, boat, ski, and swim! Just across Pequaywan Lake Road is 200 acres of State land to explore. Peaceful and serene, are you ready for a rural lifestyle? Call for a private showing today.

description: Recently sold: $875,000. Did you ever in your wildest dreams imagine that you could have everything you desired and more in your dream home? description: Recently sold: $500,000. A breakaway portion of the previous 100+ year old Whiteside Forest Estate, this property is a 2 parcel -56 acre gorgeous retreat-blessed with wildlife, old growth pines, other mature trees, trails, water accesses, and fresh Minnesota air.  Here-you can put your personal roots down and own your own piece of heaven on earth.  You can love your life in a perfect 3000 sq ft 3 Bdrm, 3 Ba hand built custom log home. Located off the Normanna Road, 18 miles from downtown Duluth, this home will surely check all of your "we have to have" or "I want" boxes! This home and it's outbuildings are very well crafted and maintained, with high quality materials throughout.  As you open the door from the impressive front porch area, pride in ownership shows and you will be greeted by a welcoming and impressive foyer with ample closet space for all of your coats, boots & shoes. Then as you enter the spacious and bright living room your will note new carpet and a stone wood fireplace. You will instantly see the craftsmanship of the log work and beautiful open vaulted ceilings that will naturally carry your eye up to the cozy loft area. Then to the left adjacent to the dining room, there is a cook's kitchen that was remodeled in 2009 with hardwood floors, hickory cabinetry, center island breakfast bar, Staron counter tops, and stainless steel appliances.  As an extension to your home, on the W side, there is a sprawling bright and cheery 4 season sun room with newer thermopane windows that bring the outdoor views inside all year round.  On the opposite side of this floor there is a main floor master suite with private deck, large walk in closet, and private bath.  A convenient laundry area and a ½ bath complete this floor.  Stepping down to the walkout LL you will find a family room with new carpet and freestanding wood stove,  2 warm LL Bedrooms with daylight windows, a full updated bath and great storage with wine cellar and workshop.  Do not miss the important fact that there is a new 50 year Owens Corning architectural shingle roof, many new windows, paved circular drive, compliant septic system, passing water tests, and new radon mitigation system.  Outside and on the grounds there is more:  A 24x34 detached garage,  22x22 garage, 12x14 heated greenhouse, fenced raised garden beds, a water feature, and fruit trees! Your dock area will take you by canoe on the Silver Pond, connecting then to the Cloquet River and on to Island Lake! + there is a private shooting range on the 40 acre parcel- This home truly is a gem!

description: Recently sold: $385,000. One of Duluth's most stately homes on Waverly Avenue in the Fryberger woods area of Hunter's Park!  This lovely Victorian era "stick style" home was built in 1894 and features tall ceilings and original woodwork including hardwood floors throughout, pocket doors, window and floor molding, staircase, columns, bead board, and wainscot in the dining room.  The main floor has a foyer with a stunning carved oak grand staircase with a small arched alcove and original detailed oak front door with an oval window.  There are three living areas, a formal front parlor, center living room with a custom Finnish wood burning stove, plus a bonus area that could be used as a music room, sitting room or play area for the kids, the eat-in kitchen has oak cabinetry, a tiled backsplash and Fisher and Paykel dish drawers, a mudroom addition with built-in benches, and a half bath is just off the kitchen.  An opulent formal dining room is adjacent to the kitchen and features French doors, custom wainscot, a gorgeous cove ceiling with a center ceiling medallion and a brass chandelier.  There is a small alcove flanked with carved corbels, plus the original built-in is stored in the basement.  Up the stairs to the second floor you will find a cozy master bedroom with a fireplace and a completely remodeled on suite bathroom beautifully done with marble tiles throughout, custom glass shower door, period style fixtures plus the original medicine cabinet remains.  There are four additional spacious bedrooms and a full bath with colorful tile in the hallway.  Continue up to the third floor to the large finished bonus area complete with ceiling fans plus tons of built in storage!  Plenty of light floods into this home with its abundance of windows.  The exterior of this large home is stucco with wood trim, the addition off the back is low maintenance vinyl.  In the front of the home is a three season enclosed porch which is surrounded with windows plus there's a sizable deck with low maintenance decking off the kitchen area.  The oversized lot is partially fenced and is complete with a two stall detached garage, paved drive, wood storage area plus plenty of room for outdoor entertaining and gardening.

description: Recently sold: $175,000. Charming Turn of the Century Traditional Home! Located high on the top of Minneapolis St in the Woodland Neighborhood of Duluth. Unique additional features include upper balcony, open front porch, paved drive, extra living space above the outside storage building and a partial view.  Property has an active rental license, closing subject to lease terms and notice requirement. Property has been well cared. A few updates include vinyl windows, infloor heat, newer roof, exterior and interior paint, but with a 100 year old home it does have some continued maintenance needs and is priced accordingly.

Recently sold: $363,000. Gourmet Kitchen.  Solid wood floors.
All cabinets custom made.
Central air conditioning. A great neighborhood.

https://sites.google.com/gerlachbeaumier.com/for-sale-by-owner/home

Priced less than recent appraisal
      ** Owner willing to work with buyers with or without agents
This five bed, three bath home with gas forced air heat and central air conditioning with a walkout.  Low utility costs with a two year old furnace and one year old gas hot water heater, this home has three heating and cooling zones along with a wood burning fireplace insert for a warm, cozy living space.  With two dining areas and a peninsula for bar stools, both family meals and entertaining are a breeze.  Add the well planned kitchen with a deep copper sink, and Wolf, Subzero and Asko appliances and cooking is fun with easy clean up. And don't forget the large 12' x 30' deck overlooking a back yard full of maple trees which provide shade and privacy in summer and solar warmth in winter.

description: Recently sold: $416,500. Do you seek a "close, quiet country setting" with plenty of opportunity for enjoying your own outdoors setting? This 4 BR/4 BA home will impress you! Just 5 miles from downtown Duluth, it's a place where everyone can be comfortable. Within 10 minutes you can reach the mall area or the North Shore--excellent central location and Ridgeview Golf Course in Duluth is just a few blocks away! Situated on 3 acres, you'll love this home's smart floor plan with the "great room" concept that features and eat-in kitchen at the center of life + family room with gas fireplace & access to the deck. The comfy living-dining combo features a vaulted ceiling and wood-burning FP. Mud room/laundry are adjacent to the attached garage, while upstairs you have privacy for your 3 bedrooms & 2 baths. The owner's suite offers a walk-in closet and spacious 3/4 bath. Head downstairs and you'll LOVE the rec room that walks out the back yard. There's another nice bedroom and 3/4 bath plus a flexible space that's currently used as an office. Don't miss the dream shed out back. New furnace, water heater, water softener. HSA home warranty included.

Recently sold: $270,151. HUGE REDUCTION! WALK INTO MAJOR EQUITY! MUST SEE BEFORE GONE! This is a great place to call home! Stunning 4 BR 3 BA Contemporary located close to town on 4.77 acres. Open floor plan with slate floors in kitchen breakfast bar. Dining area has wet bar patio doors which lead to 2 tiered deck overlooking front pond. Sunken LR w vault ceiling, gorgeous stone wood burning fireplace. Lg main floor BR BA, laundry rm, addition w office huge fam area spectacular 25x17 master suite w corner gas frplc, walk-in closet, full bath w Jacuzzi tub sliding doors to private deck overlooking private wooded backyard. 2 car detached garage w woodstove another 3 car detached w furnace 2 lg office areas.

description: Recently sold: $600,000. A Gem!!   Magnificent Lake Superior views -40 beautiful luscious acres with apple trees, many garden areas and trails.  You will surely want to see this perfect close-country charming home!  Described by Sharon Ross, Architecture Magazine, as A North Shore home set atop a high point site in Duluth -close to town with magnificent southern views of Lake Superior and Western views of hills and sunsets -with Danish tradition and an eclectic twist... This warm, unique, solid, and sunny 3+ bedroom 3 bath home with different shapes, angles and forms, was carefully designed by David Salmela and Cheryl Fosdick and custom crafted by Builders Commonwealth.  The interior features a sprawling main level with welcoming foyer, large closets, and a brick accent wall, separating the large dining area from the living room.  This main floor also boasts a spacious kitchen with breakfast nook area and built ins, an office, a Master suite with bath and 2 closets. Upstairs you will find 2 additional large bedrooms with skylights, nice storage spaces, and a full bath.  Zoned Hot water heat throughout, in floor heat in the kitchen, dining room and foyer, +passive sunshine heat in the winter, and custom roller shades create the perfect temperatures throughout the year.   One must see to appreciate the love & thought that went into the design of this lovely , "enveloped in sunshine" -home!  The Location of this property  is perfect, actually priceless- as it is just minutes to town! Also: Additional 24.47 acres available - 07490 (17.01 acres  access off of Jean Duluth Rd and 07520 7.46 acres  (has 2 bldgs on it)-previously part of lakewood berry farms.  Septic will be replaced!

description: Recently sold: $315,000. 3867 Fauvelle Rd, Rice Lake/Duluth $314,900-4BR, 3BA, 5 ACRES. Pole barn, great yard, patio, walk-out bsmnt, family rm, brkfst nook, formal dng rm, large master bdrm. (#6083713)

Recently sold: $723,000. This fabulous home was designed & built by Ray Moe, one of this area's premier contractors. The building site was chosen on this 11-acre parcel to maximize the views of Lake Superior. Are you a star gazer? You'll enjoy the beautiful and ever-changing skies by day and by night, as well as the colors of the forest with the changing of the seasons. Watch ships enter and depart the local harbors! No detail has been overlooked in this elegant yet comfortable home. Cherry cabinetry and birch flooring throughout are the first indication of the thoughtfulness and quality that went into the making of it. Clever accent lighting, surround sound, granite, Andersen Windows, Trex decking--the list goes on. Lower level has in-floor heat, upper level is gently heated by vents hidden under window sills. The room currently used as an office is sound-proofed. Handsome gardens surround the home, and nature abounds. You'll LOVE the privacy and the convenience of being 15 minutes from Downtown Duluth. Call! Brokered And Advertised By: Edina Realty, Inc - Duluth Listing Agent: Sheryl Homan

description: Recently sold: $420,000. Have you ever wanted to buy a property on a beautiful private lake, that you could use when you wanted but also create a space for others to use and gain income? Then Briar Lake Lodge is for you! Currently used as a VRBO.. Imagine the feeling of hot summer days fishing, boating, snowmobiling, skiing, snowshoeing and outdoor lifestyles that some can only dream of. This space is so unique, perhaps we have captured the feeling through photographs, but seeing and experiencing the space for yourself is a must. Close to town, about 30 minutes from Duluth with tons of outdoor activities right here! This year-round lodge has room for everyone! With 5 bedrooms a great master bedroom with a sauna and plenty of room. The grand living room with windows all around to draw in the beauty of woods, the lake and peace. The stunning stone fireplace will provide hours of enjoyment with family and friends gathered around. The kitchen is so cool! The stone wall, the long galley style with a cozy formal dining room just off one side. The grounds hold a special little one room guest cabin with loads of space for outdoor dining, fire pits and yard games. Pitch a tent under the trees, hoist a hammock, the ideas are endless! Close to the road is a huge 6 stall garage, with two stalls separated so one can keep part of it heated. We have kept the useful "outhouse" on site for obvious reasons, it's handy! So, there you have it. Please call listing agent for a private tour of this grand old lodge waiting for new memories to be created.... Also, the bonus here, seller is willing to carry a contract for deed!

description: Recently sold: $477,500. Welcome to the beautiful King's Court neighborhood where you get the best of both worlds! Private 10 acre wooded lot with just the right amount of neighbors.  This 4 bedroom, 3 bathroom executive custom built home has everything you're looking for.  You'll be amazed when you enter through the double doors into a large, inviting open foyer.  On the main level is a beautiful hickory kitchen with quartz counter tops, center island, dining room looking into a private backyard, hickory hardwood floors, floor to ceiling stone fireplace, and lots of natural light.  On the other side of the home you have 3 large bedrooms and a gorgeous bathroom with a jetted tub and custom tile shower.  Upstairs is your own private en suite master bedroom, which was recently updated in 2018.  The master is absolutely stunning with vaulted ceilings, gas fireplace, his and her walk-in closets, built in book shelves, tile bathroom flooring, soaking tub, custom built glass shower and much more. This home also has a partially finished basement that you can add your own finishing touches to make it yours! Don't forget that there is also an over-sized 3 car heated garage and a 12'x32' custom built shed for your toys.  Recent updates include a brand new high efficiency furnace and a maintenance free steel roof. This close country home is a dream come true.

description:
Recently sold: $360,400. YOUR SEARCH IS OVER! Pride of ownership definitely shines through on this amazing Hunters Park 3 bdrm, 3 bath ranch. From the spacious vaulted & slate-tiled foyer to the open concept living, dining and living room, this property has all the space you will need to entertain successfully. All 3 bedrooms are located on the main level and the over-sized master bedroom has an very generous walk-in closet, access to a patio area, a brand new bath featuring tiled floor and shower areas with stacked stone accents, deep soaking tub, dual sinks and separate walk-in shower. The living areas have vaulted ceilings, a gas fireplace, a casual dining area, S/S appliances & breakfast bar. The hickory kitchen cabinets, flooring and ceilings give this home a Northern Minnesota vibe, yet offers a very warm & contemporary feel at the same time. The lower level keeps this theme flowing with a tiled floor rec room and wainscoted walls. The newly remodeled full bath is great for accommodating over-night guests and the laundry is conveniently located just steps away from the bath. The sellers painstakingly spent many hours creating a larger park-like back yard by removing numerous tress, laying new sod/seed, expanding the patio area and meticulously maintaining the 
landscaping. How about we add seamless gutters/downspouts, a 30' X 23' attached garage, a finished & heated 2 car garage, new light fixtures, Andersen windows and a very sought-after location! This home has it all and won't last long! Set up you private showing today!

description: Recently sold: $200,000. A Job transfer gives you the opportunity to be the next owner of this fantastic 3 bdrm, 2 bath ranch! This home is located in the well-established Woodland neighborhood and boasts an abundance of amenities for all to enjoy. The main floor offers an eat-in kitchen with dishwasher and GE 4 burner gas stove, formal dining room with access to the covered breezeway, generous living room with a gas fireplace and a wall of built-ins, 2 of the 3 bedrooms and a full bath.  As you descend the stairs to the basement, you will be pleasantly surprised to see a wonderful rec room with a Franklin-style gas stove and plenty of space to entertain, down the hall is the 3rd bedroom (non legal), a 3/4 bath, laundry room and a sauna (currently used as storage).  There is an over-sized 2 car garage with a workshop space and manicured, level 66x 153 lot. All you need to do is move in and start enjoying life!  DO NOT HESITATE, as this one is priced to sell immediately!

description: Recently sold: $314,000. Country Living just minutes from town. Check out this 3 bedroom 1 and 3/4 bath super-efficient single level home that was built in 2002. This home was built by builder Harry Pearson for himself, he used structural insulated panel walls, some of the other features include in floor heat, Marvin windows, there is a 3-sided propane fireplace shared by the living room and dining room which also have vaulted ceilings. There is a bright cozy sun-room off the dining room that has a wood fireplace. The custom kitchen has newer granite counter tops and newer appliances. There is a heated 2-car attached garage with a walk-up storage area and there is also a 2-car detached garage. You have an asphalt driveway with a 25-foot concrete apron by the attached garage. The roof was replaced with 35-year architectural shingles in September of 2016. The nicely wooded 5 acres has a pond and there is a fenced in garden with a shed. If you would like you can hit the state snowmobile trails, they are right out of your back yard, the owner has planted trees on the back of the lot so you really can't hear them. Don't miss this one..

description: Recently sold: $325,000. 6607 Sumac Dr is a 4 bed, 3 bath home with a 2 car heated garage on 3 acres of land! This lovely and well-kept home has an open floor plan with vaulted ceilings and big windows offering views of the lake. Sliding doors off of the living room lead out to a large deck with more lake views - a great spot to grill out this summer! Nice outdoor patio as well. The basement was finished 5 years ago, and includes a big family/rec room, laundry room, bathroom, plenty of storage space, and a bedroom big enough that it could be split into two rooms for a 5th bedroom. Central air throughout. Heated shop with toilet and workbench, and a smaller garage door for ATVs or snowmobiles. Lovely landscaping with gardens and rock bed. The location and acreage provides plenty of privacy and a safe place for kids to run and play. And just 30 minutes from downtown Duluth, you will have the enjoyment of country living close to town - the best of both worlds!

description: Recently sold: $495,000. Welcome to 237 Fairmont St - one of Duluth's most iconic and unique homes! Completely surrounded by nature, this gorgeous, architecturally designed masterpiece is truly one of a kind. The lot features Tischers Creek frontage, panoramic views, it abuts Hartley Park, and the Coggs Duluth Traverse Bike Trail and the Superior Hiking Trail are right outside the door. The yard is all natural so no mowing is required and the private fire pit and ponds provide a heavenly sanctuary. This modern contemporary home features quality construction with huge windows overlooking land and wildlife, there are 3+ bedrooms, 4 baths, a master suite w/ a walk-in closet, a family room, and a library. The open feel with huge windows in every room will take your breath away. The sound mechanicals and extremely energy efficient heating system will add to your year round enjoyment of this incredible home. Although the privacy and nature surrounding makes it feel like you're out in the country, this home is conveniently located in town and near all amenities. This one is a must see!

description: Recently sold: $259,000. Welcome to Historical Hunter's Park, a neighborhood rich in history! One of the "Street Car Suburbs" of the 1890's this area was built by mining and railroad wealth. This lovely folk victorian home was built by J.R. Quigley ( a well-known builder in Duluth) for J.G. Bowers. The pride in workmanship is very apparent as you enter in the foyer, with 9' ft ceilings, a Queen Anne era inspired spindles on the staircase and a "water closet" 1/2 bath. Through the leaded glass french doors, you are greeted into the enchanting parlor with a solarium that peers out to the English gardens in the side yard. A yesteryear must to a modern plus, you can multi-purpose this area as a yoga/zen room or home office. The grand pocket doors open to the formal living room, with a gorgeous gas fireplace, hardwood floors, oversized windows, cool contemporary wall color, a truly elegant space. The owners have re-arranged the formal dining room and kitchen, which is now an open concept, and a perfect fit for today's busy lives. A Breakfast bar, Butler's pantry, and mud room complete this area. The second floor hosts a timeless master bedroom with the original fireplace, wrapped in glass tiles, the tri-windows let in plenty of natural light and two closets. The three other bedrooms also have tall windows and plenty of closet space. A full bath with a jetted tub and an amazing laundry room complete this level. On the third floor, up the servant's staircase to a huge area where you can watch TV or play games plus another bedroom, a huge bonus. The property has an 1890's screen house, with the invention of wire mesh in the 1890's a screened house on those hot Duluth days you could walk the gardens and take lemonade in this cool relaxing area. There is a 2 car and 1 car detached garages to the back of the property. There is a shared driveway, making it half the snow blowing work. Enjoy the close proximity to Hartley Nature Park, shopping, schools, trails, and so much more. An opportunity not to miss, call now for a private showing.

description: Recently sold: $370,000. CLOSE COUNTRY! This lovingly maintained home close to Homecroft School is only five minutes from the intersection of Kenwood and Arrowhead roads. You'll love how close you are to town, and the privacy the 2.5 acre lot has to offer. Not only is there a newer deck, but also a newer patio, and they both run the length of the home - wow! When you walk through the door, it's obvious how open and spacious the floor plan is. There's a gas fireplace and wet bar in the main level family room and an open concept second level. No matter what the weather is like, there's plenty of comfortable space here for gathering and entertaining! Three of the five bedrooms have access to their own bathrooms, so when it's time to retreat after a busy day every member of your family and/or guests will have their privacy. Tile in the bathrooms, a granite counter top with double sinks, and a custom birch vanity in the main bathroom are additional amenities. The second living space in the basement gives everyone a chance to spread out. You can even eat your own eggs, made possible by the chick coop out back!

description: Recently sold: $216,900. Nicely perched at the end of the dead-end road sits this updated 3 bedroom house. Upstairs you will find 3 bedrooms the main bedroom is large in size, all fully carpeted. Full bath with nice updates. Downstairs is a family room with tasteful updates, a large utility room with laundry, workshop space and storage space. A really nice high efficiency boiler. A great all around house with all the right updates.

description: For sale: $569,000. Looking for a home on a lake with privacy but is still close to town? 6901 Bear Island Rd is a 4-bedroom, 3-bathroom home with a 2 car attached and a 2 car detached garage (with shop area) sitting 220' of Island Lake shore and is ready to be yours! Walking inside this home, you are welcomed by a spacious foyer, natural sunlight and beautiful hardwood flooring that flows throughout the main level. Off the foyer, you have a bedroom and a ¾ bathroom. You have a large living room on the main level that offers enough space for everyone to enjoy, open to the kitchen and dining room and amazing view of the spacious backyard and of Island Lake! With the kitchen being open to the living room and dining room, it is perfect for entertaining friends and family! There is a large amount of countertop space for prepping snacks and meals, breakfast bar, a large amount of cabinet storage space and views of the lake! Off the dining room, there is a sunroom, perfect for those days you want to relax and watch the sunsets! The master bedroom is on the main level and is a sizable room! There is a full master bathroom with separate double vanity sinks, a jacuzzi tub, a large walk-in closet and your main level laundry. A mudroom and an office are also on the main level. Going to the lower level, you are given an extra large family room! There is a second kitchen in the lower level, eat-in area and a sitting area that offers a gas fireplace! Two additional bedrooms and a ¾ bathroom are on the lower level. A great feature to this home is an at-home gym/workout room that has a hot tub!! There is a large utility room, storage space in the utility room and a walkout. Throughout this home, you will love all the space that is given, the amazing views and the lake that is right in your backyard. You will love the heated detached garage that has a workshop space, the attached heated garage and yard space! Enjoy the main level back deck and the lower level walkout during those warm summer days! Mature apple trees along the gradual decline yard to the private beach. This house will fit everyone needs to grow into and a great place to call home!!

description: Recently sold: $605,000. Country living in the city with a great valley view. This 3 bdrm 2 bath home is situated on 3.3 beautiful wooded acres. The kitchen is newly updated with custom Hickory cabinetry and granite counter tops. There is a handy breakfast bar and a formal dining area with glass doors to the deck, perfect for grilling or just a quiet cup of coffee. The upstairs bath has custom hickory cabinetry and a new vanity top. The 3 bdrms are all on the main floor. The lower level family room has brand new carpet and a Lopi fireplace for cozy fall and winter nights. A large activity room is waiting for your workout equipment or maybe a pool table and there is a handy walk-out which makes it a quick commute to the garage. This home has replacement windows, a 2+ car garage and additional storage. Garden area with apple and plum trees, blueberry and raspberry bushes and an agricultural well for watering. Septic has been tested. Brokered And Advertised By: Edmunds Company, LLP Listing Agent: Cheryl Morinville

description: Recently sold: $350,000. 4236 Normanna Rd is a beautiful, spacious home on more than 9 acres of land in Rural Duluth! This home has everything you need on the main floor, and a bright, wide open feel with an open floor plan and lots of big windows to bring in natural light. This pine-covered property has easy access to lakes and hiking, biking, and snowmobile trails, with additional trails right on the property. Three decks and a screen house give you plenty of opportunity to enjoy nature right outside your door. Paved roads all the way to the house that are plowed promptly in winter. The extra large 30x32 3 stall garage offers plenty of room for cars and storage. This home has updates galore - recent updates include: new septic line & water heater (2012), new sliding glass door (2016), new garage roof (2016), fresh exterior paint house & garage (2016), freshly painted decks (2017), new dishwasher & microwave (2017), fresh interior paint in most of the house (downstairs in 2017; upstairs done just before listing), and new downstairs carpet (2017). House roof was also redone in 2010. Updated bathroom (2014) with walk in shower, plus an extra heater to keep this room warm and cozy. Newer stainless steel appliances, Corian counter tops. Owners will also be replacing the upstairs carpet and the sliding glass door off of the master bedroom over the next few weeks.

description: Recently sold: $249,900. Sitting on a beautiful over-sized corner lot in Hunters Park, this 2++ bedroom, 2 bath home has so much to offer. The kitchen features Silestone countertops, hi-end SS appliances, incl. an LG 3-door frig & separate wine frig, & SS deep sink w/ gooseneck spring spout faucet. Almost all the floors have been replaced & even the moldings and door casings were completely re-done with a handsome dark distressed wood and unique wainscoting in the formal dining room. Both baths have also had extensive remodeling:The main floor full bath now features marble on the floors & tub surround, as well as a blown-glass vessel sink, & the completely new 3/4 bath in the LL features stunning & unique tiling, with an over-sized glassed-in shower, w/ ledge seat & pebbled floor & 2 ceiling- mounted rain shower-heads. Currently the 2 LL BRs do not have egress windows, but the wells have been excavated. And the pretty treed lot features a paver patio & firepit & great 1 1/2 story shed/workshop. Move right in! Brokered And Advertised By: Overman Company Listing Agent: Tiss Underdahl

description: Recently sold: $305,000. Come and check out this one owner, beautifully updated home just outside of town with an open floor plan, lots of windows that provide a ton of natural light, and a large Master bedroom and bath, plus two plus more spacious bedrooms.  Imagine enjoying this spectacular home in a quiet neighborhood that offers a fabulous place for the family to gather upstairs and down.  This home offers two family rooms, one with a beautiful fireplace and bar. Appreciate the brand new kitchen counters, lots of cabinet space, a breakfast bar, updated appliances & convection oven.  Both bathrooms have been updated, and the siding has been replaced in 2018.  This home has loads of storage inside and out and is also equipped with WiFi connected Thermostat, Garage Door, and Sump Pump. The Garage also has battery back up if you lost power and has pull down stairs that lead up to more storage. There are apple trees that produce the best apples for pies, and a small garden filled with strawberries and rhubarb. Gorgeous landscaping is starting to come to life and the yard will fill with flowers, beautiful bushes, hastas, tons of wild flowers (including lupin), and there is a highly sought after secret "guest" that grows wild on the property.  This home is centrally located just minutes from shopping, restaurants, schools, and of course the beautiful Hartley Park. Owners are disappointed to be leaving this home, and must move due to employment requirements.  Priced to sell.

description: Recently sold: $385,000. Looking for a property that has everything for everyone? Welcome to 5270 Arnold Road. Let's start with the "man cave" a 40 x 60 heated slab pole barn with a 1/2 bath; you will want for nothing here. How about mom/dad, there is a fantastic mother-in-law apartment with kitchen, living room, bath & bed. The main living space is the open concept with gas fireplace, new kitchen, a lovely master suite with private bath, another bedroom and 3/4 bath. The lower has a huge family room! description: Recently sold: $187,957. Do you have a wish list for your new home? Do you want a turn key with character and charm? Then this Hunter's Park jewel promises to impress! A solid 1920's traditional Sherburne design, offers 4 bedrooms,2 baths, a modified open floor plan, stunning hardwood floors, large windows, 8 ft ceilings, pleasing wall colors, 1800+ sq.ft.& a fully fenced backyard w/a Trex deck. A covered veranda invites you into the home + its a perfect place for relaxing. On the main floor, is a delightful foyer, the living & dining rooms are spacious w/sizable windows that let in tons of natural light, and a charming classic kitchen w/ an awesome pantry!  The upper level hosts 3 bedrooms w/hardwoods, ample closet space, a full bath & a charming shaker porch! The lower level has a huge family room, a bedroom, & laundry area. There is oodles of storage space here and in the 1+ car garage. The location is sublime, close to schools, Hartley Field, trails, shopping, Blue Stone Complex & bus line! See it today!
